<br>
My understanding is that the parchments are NO DROP but the resulting spell is tradeable.  This allows the frontrunners to make a decent profit off of their efforts and adventurousness.<br>
<br>
Before you know it there will be 61+ spells for sale in the bazaar.  Lots of them.  Many will sell for 25pp (or just above what an NPC will give you for them).<br>
<br>
If they dropped like candy then they would be worth nothing.<br>
<br>
I do dislike the randomness associated with the research procedure.  I hated the FV turn-in quests.  If its research, then from a role-playing standpoint, why, if you follow a procedure, are the results different when the same procedure is followed verbatim?  There should be a set of ingredients and actions that lead to a specific result EVERY TIME.<br>
<br>
I also believe that a *few* of the results should be NO DROP spells, to allow those who made the effort to learn research to distinguish themselves.  However, I know that viewpoint is unpopular, and will not push it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
